Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In a small bowl, pour stuffing mix and water. Bake until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean and the top springs back when lightly pressed - about 1 hour 15 minute. Lift off the pan and cool the cake upright on the rack for at least 30 minutes before serving.

In a heavy-bottomed pot over medium, fry the bread until crisp. Remove the bread from the pot and drain on paper towels. Saute the onion and garlic in the bread grease over low heat until soft, about 3 minutes. Add the brussels sprouts and stir them around so that they are coated with the bread grease. Add the broth and cook, covered, over low heat until the sprouts are easily pierced with a fork, about 12-15 minutes. Stir in the butter just before serving. Garnish each serving with bacon bits.
Place the chicken in a large bowl and add the lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Add to the chicken and mix well. Bake for 20-25 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly.

Preheat oven to 350f and oil a 9-inch round cake pan. Remove zest from all oranges and juice from one. Set fruit aside for another use. In a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat eggs and salt together until frothy and light. Slowly add sugar while continuing to mix. Mix about 1 more minute. In a side bowl, mix olive oil, citrus zest and juice. Using a spoon, stir this into the egg mixture, just folding until all inches. Pour batter into prepared pan and place in oven and bake 50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool to room temperature, cut into wedges and serve.

In a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, unsifted flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, milk, egg, vegetable oil. Mix well. Cover and simmer over low heat 10-15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat, stir in chopped chives and serve.

Preheat oven to 375f. Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Add the flour, salt and pepper. Dredge the rabbit pieces in the seasoned flour. Combine the egg and 1 t water. Dip the rabbit pieces in the egg. Coat the pieces well with bread crumbs. Brown on all sides in the hot lard or bacon drippings. Slowly add 1 c water to the skillet and cover tightly. Simmer 1 hour or more until tender.

Preheat oven to 350. Mix together first 5 ingredients in a bowl and pour into greased baking dish. Slice walnuts into chunks and place on top of bean mixture. Cover and bake at 350 for 45 minutes. Remove cover for last 15 minutes to brown the franks.

Place skinless chicken breast in a large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add garlic cloves and sauté until fragrant, about 5 minutes. Combine the water, dark brown sugar, heavy cream, ground cinnamon, vanilla extract, egg, strawberry, whipped cream and vanilla extract in a medium bowl. Pour the syrup over the pancakes and top with whipped cream. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden on each side. Remove from oven and cool completely.

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. In a glass baking dish, squeeze the juice of one lemon. Add the olive oil. Put the fillets in the dish and rub the lemon oil mixture on both sides. Add salt and pepper to taste. Take large spoonfuls of the spinach, sauce and cheese and place in the center of each fillet. Roll up each fillet and secure with a toothpick. Add remaining ingredients in between and on top of the fillets. And squeeze the second lemon on top. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes.
